<h2 class="bold font-l">Canary in a Sewer</h2>
<p class="_pmvv-vidbox-descTxt">
Goblin Slayer brings a canary with him to detect poison gas. However, real canaries typically STOP singing when they're affected by poison gas. </p>
</div>
<div class="video-examples-thumbs">
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="004p87" data-video-descrip="Claude says that if you cook with gas in a poorly-ventilated caravan, you'll choke like a canary." data-video-title="Claude the Cat" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/004p87_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/004p87.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/CanaryInACoalMine" data-video-tropename="Canary in a Coal Mine" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="Advertising/ClaudeTheCat" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/004p87.jpg">
<p><span class="bold">Claude the Cat</span></p>
</a>
<a href="#video-link" data-video-id="o8laks" data-video-descrip="Sammy J uses a canary to test of his man-made mineshaft is safe." data-video-title="Good News Week" data-video-url="https://d1w6li7s85ibls.cloudfront.net/qvbr/o8laks_640x360p_qvbr.mp4" data-video-thumbnail="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/o8laks.jpg" data-video-trope="Main/CanaryInACoalMine" data-video-tropename="Canary in a Coal Mine" data-video-approval="APPROVED" data-video-troper-rating="" data-video-average-rating="" data-video-rating-count="" data-video-media-sources="Creator/RandyFeltface,Series/GoodNewsWeek" class="video-launch-link video-overlay-link video-background-image lazy-image" data-src="https://static.tvtropes.org/trope_videos_transcoded/images/sd/o8laks.jpg">
